All Characters:  Name: Lucius Draven
Civilization: Audorms
Age: 42
Profession: Military General
Background:
Lucius Draven is a respected and formidable military general within the Audorm civilization. With a strong military background and unwavering loyalty to his civilization, Lucius has risen through the ranks to become a prominent figure in Audorm society. He is known for his strategic thinking, leadership skills, and unwavering dedication to the principles and values of the Audorm civilization.

Strengths:
Strategic and Tactical Mind: Lucius possesses a brilliant strategic and tactical mind, allowing him to devise effective battle plans and outmaneuver his opponents. He can analyze complex situations and make calculated decisions that maximize the strength of his forces.
Military Expertise: Having dedicated his life to military training and service, Lucius has a deep understanding of warfare, weaponry, and combat techniques. He excels in leading troops into battle, coordinating movements, and employing various military strategies.
Discipline and Determination: Lucius is known for his unwavering discipline and determination. He sets high standards for himself and his subordinates, instilling a strong sense of loyalty and dedication within his troops. He leads by example and inspires those around him to give their best in the face of adversity.

Weaknesses:
Rigid Adherence to Tradition: Lucius can be rigid in his adherence to traditional Audorm customs and values, sometimes resisting change or alternative viewpoints. This can create conflicts with individuals who challenge the status quo or propose alternative approaches to solving problems.
Tendency to Prioritize Military Might: Due to his military background, Lucius tends to prioritize military strength and the use of force as solutions to conflicts. This can lead to clashes with those who advocate for more diplomatic or peaceful approaches.
Limited Perspective: Lucius' focus on military matters and his role as a military general can sometimes limit his perspective on broader societal issues. He may overlook the nuances and complexities of non-military aspects of governance and societal development.

Dark Secrets:
Hidden Agendas: Lucius harbors hidden agendas and personal ambitions that go beyond his military duties. He may be willing to make sacrifices or compromise ethical principles to achieve his personal goals.
Past Trauma: Lucius carries deep emotional scars from past conflicts or traumatic events, which have shaped his worldview and approach to leadership. These hidden wounds may influence his decisions and actions in unexpected ways.

Motivation: Lucius Draven is the antagonist in the story due to his strong belief in the natural order of the Convergence and his determination to prevent any interference. While the main characters are driven by a desire to understand and influence the Convergence for the betterment of JunJia Prime, Lucius sees their actions as a threat to the Audorm civilization and its values. He views the Convergence as a test of strength and resilience, and believes that any attempt to alter or manipulate it goes against the traditions and teachings of the Audorms. Lucius becomes the primary source of conflict, constantly challenging the motivations and actions of the main characters, and working to thwart their efforts. His role as the antagonist adds tension and opposition to the story, highlighting the differing perspectives and ideologies surrounding the Convergence.
Lucius Draven's character embodies the strength, discipline, and military prowess of the Audorm civilization. His strengths, weaknesses, and hidden secrets contribute to the complexity and conflict within the story of JunJia Prime.

